<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="414" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,721,2008]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,721,747]" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Ocherous to brownish species with unpatterned wing except stigma (
<figureCitation box="[1047,1136,722,748]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1693,1717]" captionTargetBox="[155,1424,509,1656]" captionTargetId="figure-190@14.[151,1435,489,1669]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 8. Protohelius japonicus sp. nov. (A–E, G–H) and P. tinkhami Alexander, 1938 (F, traced from the holotype slide): A, habitus (male); B, wing; C, male terminalia, dorsal view; D, sternite 9, ventral view; E, outer and inner gonostyli, outer surface; F, lobe of gonostylus; G, aedeagal complex, dorsal view; H, ibid, lateral view (left = dorsal). Scale bars: A–B, 2 mm; C–H, 0.1 mm (not given in F)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6902808" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6902808/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">Fig. 8A</figureCitation>
). Vertex at narrowest point 1.5 times as wide as scape. Presutural area of mesonotum with three dark stripes. Scutal lobe and mediotergite mainly dark brown. Legs generally yellowish. Cell m 
<subScript attach="left" box="[743,769,812,826]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="414">1+2</subScript>
2–3 times as long as cell dm. Abdomen weakly dark toward distal segment, yellowish on basal sternites. Lobe of gonostylus with outer lobe not distinctly wide on distal part, inner lobe 3/5 length of outer one.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
